{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014juknVQZJAHybEYtToB27V","type":"tool_result","content":"# imgui-bundle: Cross-Platform GUI Development\n\n**imgui-bundle** is a Python and C++ toolkit for building graphical user interfaces with minimal setup. According to the documentation, it's designed to help developers \"Start your first app in 5 lines of code, or less.\"\n\n## Key Features\n\nThe library emphasizes ease of use through the Immediate Mode GUI (IMGUI) paradigm. It supports multiple platforms including Windows, Linux, macOS, iOS, Android, and WebAssembly.\n\nNotable capabilities include:\n\n- **Rapid prototyping**: Minimal code required to create functional GUIs\n- **Extensive widget library**: Includes plotting, node editing, and markdown rendering\n- **Web compatibility**: Works with Emscripten for C++ and Pyodide for Python\n- **Well-documented**: Python bindings include detailed stubs matching the C++ API\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall via pip with: `pip install imgui-bundle` or `pip install \"imgui-bundle[full]\"` for all optional features.\n\n## Current Status\n\nThe latest version is 1.92.5 (released November 25, 2025). The project maintains \"Production/Stable\" status under the MIT License, requiring Python >=3.10.\n\nThe library integrates multiple open-source projects including Dear ImGui, ImPlot, and ImGuizmo, making it a comprehensive toolkit for both research prototyping and application development."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"bf5b73a7-de23-4aa1-a64d-a02c7bcf6b5b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S47B9Sy1pjyUFRjZy6fXit","type":"tool_result","content":"# Dear ImGui Bundle Overview\n\n**Dear ImGui Bundle** is a cross-platform toolkit for C++ and Python that simplifies GUI development around the Dear ImGui library.\n\n## Core Capabilities\n\nThe framework provides \"a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python\" with integrated components including plotting (ImPlot/ImPlot3D), image inspection (ImmVision), node editors, and specialized widgets.\n\n## Platform Support\n\nThe toolkit supports Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, and WebAssembly. C++ applications compile via Emscripten for web deployment, while Python apps run in browsers through Pyodide.\n\n## Key Components\n\n- **Hello ImGui**: Manages windows, rendering backends, docking, and asset handling\n- **ImmApp**: Simplifies add-on activation for plotting and markdown support\n- **Integrated widgets**: File dialogs, knobs, spinners, toggles, and command palettes\n\n## Developer Resources\n\nThe project offers comprehensive documentation, an interactive browser-based manual with runnable examples, an online Python playground, and an AI-powered DeepWiki for questions about usage patterns.\n\n## Repository Status\n\nWith 1.1k stars and 3,088 commits, the project maintains active CI/CD pipelines covering OpenGL, Metal, DirectX, Vulkan, Emscripten, and mobile platforms."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"20384953-062b-4c18-964c-0d8b8ec85271"}
