{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012bUfpu9npnbp4LnThKuJd7","type":"tool_result","content":"# Dear ImGui Bundle Overview\n\n**Dear ImGui Bundle** is a comprehensive framework for building graphical user interfaces in C++ and Python. According to the documentation, it's described as a \"batteries included\" framework that \"bundles 20+ libraries for plotting, markdown, node editors, 3D gizmos, and more.\"\n\n## Key Characteristics\n\nThe framework emphasizes an **immediate mode paradigm** for UI development. This approach means developers write straightforward code without dealing with traditional widget hierarchies or callback systems. The documentation notes that \"state lives in your code\" and \"changes are immediate.\"\n\n### Platform Support\nThe toolkit operates across multiple platforms including Windows, Linux, macOS, iOS, Android, and WebAssembly, allowing the same codebase to run on desktop, mobile, and web environments.\n\n### Notable Features\n- **Python-first design** with complete bindings, type hints, and IDE autocompletion\n- **Cross-platform compatibility** via Emscripten or Pyodide for web deployment\n- **Auto-generated bindings** that track Dear ImGui upstream developments closely\n\n## Limitations\n\nThe documentation acknowledges that this solution may not suit projects requiring exact OS look-and-feel matching or where accessibility is critical. However, the immediate mode approach produces readable code that works well with both human developers and AI-assisted development tools."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"14d7c513-c46f-4c6d-a418-882d55341021"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012vUNWDqiRj1H9nzH4KYRth","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python GLFW backend integration example\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"},{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/blob/main/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py\"},{\"title\":\"A simple pyimgui example using the GLFW backend · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://gist.github.com/DGriffin91/c986d9bce5a0549d6e5c207261636e62\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/porting.html\"},{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/tree/main/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyimgui/pyimgui: Cython-based Python bindings for dear imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle: Dear ImGui Bundle: easily create ImGui applications in Python and C++. Batteries included!\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"ImGui integration: introduction and acknownledgements · pthom/imgui_bundle · Discussion #67\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/discussions/67\"},{\"title\":\"Registering additional callbacks to glfw without overriding previous ones. · pthom/imgui_bundle · Discussion #394\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/discussions/394\"}]\n\nI found relevant information about imgui_bundle Python GLFW backend integration. Here's what the search results show:\n\n## Overview\n\nimgui_bundle provides an example of using Dear ImGui with GLFW using a full Python backend, which is inspired from pyimgui backends and is still experimental.\n\n## Available Python Backends\n\nAt the moment, only glfw, sdl2 and pyglet are implemented for imgui_bundle's Python backends.\n\n## Integration Approaches\n\nimgui_bundle offers two main ways to work with GLFW in Python:\n\n1. **Full Python Backend**: You can use a full python backend (not using Hello ImGui or ImmApp), which gives you control of the full GUI loop, as shown in example_python_backend_glfw3.py with callbacks implemented in glfw_backend.py.\n\n2. **High-level API**: Alternatively, ImmApp (immediate App) provides an easy way to create an app with few lines of code by importing imgui and immapp, and running the gui_function.\n\n## Important Import Order\n\nIt is important to import glfw after imgui_bundle, since upon import, imgui_bundle informs glfw that it shall use its own version of the glfw dynamic library.\n\n## Example Resources\n\nThe official imgui_bundle repository contains example files at `bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py` that demonstrate GLFW backend integration with Python.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"d9df7b51-78d8-4a5d-a6f6-933546f08d9f"}
