{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HXQeeWQbu5XLtgfaVEnVDk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XhaFs12gBLYjuSCQmbx8kD","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"imgui_bundle Python API imgui.begin imgui.button imgui.slider_float widgets"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":283,"cache_creation_input_tokens":563,"cache_read_input_tokens":30566,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":563},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"f419dd57-4a11-46e7-b5d4-ac3a08b8d3da"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BW2EhHpJ8oxXwnbSvpCwE9","type":"tool_result","content":"# GlfwRenderer: GLFW Backend Implementation for ImGui\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `GlfwRenderer` class provides a GLFW-based backend for rendering ImGui interfaces in Python. It inherits from `ProgrammablePipelineRenderer` and manages window interaction, input handling, and frame rendering.\n\n## Key Components\n\n**Initialization & Window Setup**\nThe renderer initializes with a GLFW window and optionally attaches callbacks for keyboard, mouse, and window events. It sets the initial display size from the framebuffer dimensions and configures clipboard operations through ImGui's platform I/O system.\n\n**Input Processing**\nThe implementation maps GLFW key codes to ImGui key identifiers across multiple categories:\n- Control keys (Tab, Backspace, Enter, Escape)\n- Function keys (F1-F12)\n- Navigation keys (arrow keys, Page Up/Down, Home/End)\n- Numeric and keypad keys\n- Alphabetic characters\n- Modifier keys (Ctrl, Shift, Alt, Super)\n- Symbol keys and lock keys\n\n**Event Callbacks**\nThe renderer processes several event types:\n- Keyboard events with modifier key tracking\n- Character input for text entry\n- Mouse position and button events\n- Window resize events\n- Scroll wheel input\n\n**Frame Processing**\nThe `process_inputs()` method updates display metrics, computes framebuffer scaling, and manages delta time calculations for smooth animation. It retrieves window and framebuffer dimensions, applies proper scaling factors, and tracks timing between frames.\n\nThis backend enables ImGui applications to run with standard GLFW windowing while maintaining full keyboard and mouse interactivity."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"90e6face-7557-4c59-a0f8-3a4d18b386e3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XhaFs12gBLYjuSCQmbx8kD","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python API imgui.begin imgui.button imgui.slider_float widgets\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - pthom/imgui_bundle: From expressive code to powerful GUIs in no time: a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"bimpy - bundled imgui for python — bimpy documentation\",\"url\":\"https://podgorskiy.github.io/bimpy/\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle - Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyimgui/pyimgui: Cython-based Python bindings for dear imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui\"},{\"title\":\"imgui.core module — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.core.html\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/manual.html\"},{\"title\":\"ImGui integration: introduction and acknownledgements · pthom/imgui_bundle · Discussion #67\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/discussions/67\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - podgorskiy/bimpy: imgui for python\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/podgorskiy/bimpy\"}]\n\nI've found relevant information about imgui_bundle Python API. Here's what the search results show:\n\n## ImGui Bundle Overview\n\nDear ImGui Bundle is a collection of libraries around Dear ImGui, for both C++ and Python. It includes all of Dear ImGui along with a suite of additional libraries for plotting, node editing, markdown rendering, and much more.\n\n## Python API and Core Widgets\n\nThe python API closely mirrors the C++ API, and its documentation is extremely easy to access from your IDE, via thoroughly documented stub (*.pyi) files.\n\nImGui widgets functions that modify an input parameter in C++, return a tuple (changed, new_value) in python: see for example slider_float (python) vs SliderFloat (C++).\n\nThe widgets you mentioned—`imgui.begin`, `imgui.button`, and `imgui.slider_float`—are core Dear ImGui widgets that are available in the imgui_bundle Python API. You can explore core Dear ImGui widgets, and the interactive manual is intended to be your live reference: browse widgets, run demos, and copy code snippets directly into your own projects.\n\n## Key Features\n\nFull Python bindings with type hints and IDE autocompletion are provided, and Python bindings are auto-generated, ensuring they stay up-to-date with the underlying library.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"2dd5bdd5-0463-4c4b-90ae-07a648c016a3"}
