{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C2wR6EeSSMtbN1zDYq1puo","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python get_io want_capture_mouse imports from imgui_bundle\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"imgui.core module — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.core.html\"},{\"title\":\"Contents — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/\"},{\"title\":\"direct way to check which inputs ImGui wants to capture · Issue #364 · ocornut/imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ocornut/imgui/issues/364\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle - Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pthom/imgui_bundle: From expressive code to powerful GUIs in no time: a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyimgui/pyimgui: Cython-based Python bindings for dear imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui\"},{\"title\":\"WantCaptureMouse behavior · Issue #621 · ocornut/imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ocornut/imgui/issues/621\"},{\"title\":\"27. Module ImGui — mbm project 4.2.a documentation\",\"url\":\"https://mbm-documentation.readthedocs.io/en/latest/imgui.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about `imgui_bundle`, `get_io()`, and `want_capture_mouse`:\n\n## Key Information\n\n**Getting IO Context:**\nThe IO context should be accessed through the `get_io()` function. With imgui_bundle, you can import imgui using `from imgui_bundle import imgui`.\n\n**want_capture_mouse:**\n`want_capture_mouse` is a flag that manually overrides the `io.WantCaptureMouse` flag next frame, which is entirely left for your application to handle.\n\n## About imgui_bundle\n\nDear ImGui Bundle is a collection of libraries around Dear ImGui, for both C++ and Python, focusing on app development, rapid prototyping, tooling, and educational demonstrations.\n\n## Import Example\n\nBased on the documentation, the typical import structure for imgui_bundle would be:\n\n```python\nfrom imgui_bundle import imgui\n\nio = imgui.get_io()\n# Access want_capture_mouse through the io object\nwant_capture_mouse = io.want_capture_mouse\n```\n\nThe search results show that imgui_bundle provides Python bindings that follow the C++ ImGui API, so `get_io()` is the standard function to access the IO context where `want_capture_mouse` and other configuration options are available.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"85497469-ae45-45c0-bb32-173fcd72fa8f"}
