{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S1F1DRwXw7h6wAXhnx13xw","type":"tool_result","content":"# GlfwRenderer Class Overview\n\nThe `GlfwRenderer` class integrates GLFW window management with ImGui for handling user input and rendering. Here's what it provides:\n\n## Key Functionality\n\n**Initialization & Setup**: The class inherits from `ProgrammablePipelineRenderer` and accepts a GLFW window handle. It optionally attaches callbacks for keyboard, mouse, and window events, then configures clipboard functionality.\n\n**Input Mapping**: The `_map_keys()` method creates comprehensive mappings between GLFW key codes and ImGui key identifiers, covering:\n- Control keys (Tab, Backspace, Enter, Escape, etc.)\n- Function keys (F1-F12)\n- Navigation arrows and Page Up/Down\n- Numeric and keypad keys\n- All alphabetic characters\n- Modifier keys (Ctrl, Shift, Alt, Super)\n- Symbol keys and lock keys\n\n**Event Handling**: Callback methods process:\n- **Keyboard input**: Maps GLFW keys to ImGui format and handles modifier key states\n- **Character input**: Converts Unicode characters for text input\n- **Mouse movement**: Tracks cursor position when window is focused\n- **Mouse buttons**: Registers click events\n- **Scroll wheel**: Captures vertical and horizontal scroll\n- **Window resize**: Updates display dimensions\n\n**Frame Processing**: The `process_inputs()` method updates timing information, display size, and framebuffer scale each frame, ensuring ImGui receives accurate delta time calculations."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"c4ff074e-2851-4f31-b514-de8815865d84"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014kRoqFprSmDiyUK8H8edNs","type":"tool_result","content":"# ImGui/GLFW Python Backend Example Overview\n\nThis code demonstrates a complete ImGui integration using a full Python backend with GLFW and OpenGL. Here are the key components:\n\n## Initialization\nThe example starts by setting up the ImGui context and GLFW window through `impl_glfw_init()`, which creates a 1280x720 window with OpenGL 3.3 core profile support. The `GlfwRenderer` handles the backend implementation.\n\n## Frame Loop\nThe main loop follows the standard pattern:\n1. Poll events and process inputs\n2. Create a new ImGui frame\n3. Render UI elements\n4. Clear and display the frame\n\n## Widget Examples\nThe code showcases several ImGui components:\n- **Menu bar** with a File menu and Quit option\n- **Custom window** with markdown rendering support\n- **Text input** using multiline text editor\n- **Buttons** with click handling\n- **Keyboard state monitoring** displaying modifier keys (Ctrl, Alt, Shift, Super)\n- **Modal popup** that opens and closes on user interaction\n\n## Markdown Support\n\"These examples also demonstrate how to use the markdown rendering feature of ImGui Bundle.\" The implementation uses `imgui_md.render_unindented()` to display formatted text.\n\n## Platform Handling\nThe code includes a Wayland compatibility workaround to avoid context retrieval errors on certain Linux systems."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"2a51cb5b-28e2-493d-8e98-f2ed59542a1a"}
