{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013i2xFgCSBZ6UbtFER2TEAt","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python \"from imgui_bundle import\" correct import structure modules\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - pthom/imgui_bundle: From expressive code to powerful GUIs in no time: a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle - Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle - From expressive code to powerful GUIs\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"ImGui integration: introduction and acknownledgements · pthom/imgui_bundle · Discussion #67\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/discussions/67\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/quickstart.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle: Dear ImGui Bundle: easily create ImGui applications in Python and C++. Batteries included!\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/install-instructions.html\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/0.8.2/\"},{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/docs/docs_md/imgui_python_intro.md at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/blob/main/docs/docs_md/imgui_python_intro.md\"},{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's information about the correct import structure for imgui_bundle in Python:\n\n## Correct Import Structure\n\nThe correct way to import imgui_bundle modules is: `from imgui_bundle import imgui, hello_imgui`\n\n## Available Modules\n\nimgui_bundle is a Python package that unifies multiple Dear ImGui-related submodules, and you can import modules like: `imgui`, `implot`, `imgui_md`, `hello_imgui`, and `immapp`\n\n## Example Import Patterns\n\nHere are common import examples from the documentation:\n\n1. **Basic imports:**\n   from imgui_bundle import imgui, immapp\n\n2. **Importing multiple modules:**\n   from imgui_bundle import imgui, immvision, immapp, imgui_md\n\n3. **With demo utilities:**\n   from imgui_bundle import imgui, immvision, immapp, imgui_md and from imgui_bundle.demos_python import demo_utils\n\n## Important Note\n\nIt is important to import glfw after imgui_bundle, since upon import imgui_bundle informs glfw that it shall use its own version of the glfw dynamic library.\n\nThe main modules available in imgui_bundle include: `imgui`, `implot`, `imgui_md`, `hello_imgui`, `immapp`, `immvision`, and others—all imported directly from the `imgui_bundle` package.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"f4ff1f77-be23-4716-bd8b-921d2e95d710"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017fyzyLJPUpSCwoLrZpz2qb","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"imgui_bundle\" Python widgets \"slider_float\" \"color_button\" \"separator\" \"same_line\" API\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"imgui.core module — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.core.html\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/1.0.0b1/\"},{\"title\":\"concur.widgets API documentation\",\"url\":\"https://potocpav.github.io/python-concur-docs/master/widgets.html\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pthom/imgui_bundle: From expressive code to powerful GUIs in no time: a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle: Dear ImGui Bundle: easily create ImGui applications in Python and C++. Batteries included!\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"bimpy - bundled imgui for python — bimpy documentation\",\"url\":\"https://podgorskiy.github.io/bimpy/\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/doc/examples/testwindow.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/doc/examples/testwindow.py\"},{\"title\":\"tessl/pypi-imgui@2.0.x - Registry - Tessl\",\"url\":\"https://tessl.io/registry/tessl/pypi-imgui/2.0.0\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pyimgui/pyimgui: Cython-based Python bindings for dear imgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/manual.html\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive information about imgui_bundle and its Python API. Here's what the search revealed:\n\n## Overview\n\nDear ImGui Bundle is a bundle for Dear ImGui that enables creating ImGui applications in C++ and Python under Windows, macOS, and Linux.\n\n## Key Widget Functions\n\nThe search results contain references to the specific widgets you mentioned:\n\n- **slider_float**: A function that creates a float slider widget, returning a tuple of (bool changed, float value)\n- **separator**: Used to display a horizontal separator line\n- **same_line**: A function that positions the next widget on the same line, with optional position and spacing parameters\n\nThe search results show example usage of `separator()` and `same_line()` in a popup menu example where these functions control widget layout.\n\n## Python API Documentation\n\nThe python bindings are autogenerated and closely mirror the original C++ API, with fully typed bindings. The python API documentation is accessible from your IDE via thoroughly documented stub (*.pyi) files.\n\n## Color Handling\n\nWhile the search results don't specifically detail a `color_button` function, they do reference color editing widgets like `color_edit4` that handle color with alpha values.\n\nFor more detailed API documentation and examples specific to `color_button` and other widgets, you can visit the official Dear ImGui Bundle documentation at pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle or consult the interactive manual mentioned in the search results.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"3f7262ba-6758-4adf-bff6-69a707ddcc4d"}
