{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017FAMpGVpNKexFQcNTFp6A5","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"site:github.com pthom imgui_bundle Python \"imgui.begin\" \"imgui.end\" \"imgui.button\"\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/bindings/imgui_bundle/demos_python/demos_immapp/demo_docking.py at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/blob/main/bindings/imgui_bundle/demos_python/demos_immapp/demo_docking.py\"},{\"title\":\"Pythonic begin/end interface (adding \\\"with\\\" support) · Issue #255 · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/issues/255\"},{\"title\":\"Registering additional callbacks to glfw without overriding previous ones. · pthom/imgui_bundle · Discussion #394\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/discussions/394\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-switch/main.py at master · nx-python/imgui-switch\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/nx-python/imgui-switch/blob/master/main.py\"}]\n\nI found search results related to your query. The search returned several relevant sources from GitHub:\n\n1. **pthom/imgui_bundle demo code** - The first result shows Python code using imgui.button() and imgui.begin_group()/imgui.end_group() patterns, demonstrating how these functions are used in the imgui_bundle library.\n\n2. **pyimgui context manager discussion** - The second result shows an example of imgui.begin() and imgui.button() usage in Python, though this discusses the pyimgui project rather than imgui_bundle specifically.\n\n3. **imgui_bundle practical example** - The third result contains a complete example showing imgui.begin(), imgui.button(), and imgui.end() used together in a GUI function, which is a practical demonstration from the imgui_bundle project.\n\nThese results show how the imgui.begin(), imgui.button(), and imgui.end() functions are used together in Python code for creating graphical user interfaces with imgui_bundle.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"20de5597-1298-46d5-b5a1-8bef69ad1a62"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkEW2TcqdMDg5aLaubWz4r","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"imgui_bundle\" Python \"new_frame\" \"render\" GlfwRenderer frame management\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"How to use the imgui.new_frame function in imgui | Snyk\",\"url\":\"https://snyk.io/advisor/python/imgui/functions/imgui.new_frame\"},{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/blob/main/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py\"},{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"},{\"title\":\"Comprehensive Guide to ImGui and Python: Build Modern GUIs with Ease\",\"url\":\"https://betanet.net/view-post/comprehensive-guide-to-imgui-and-python\"},{\"title\":\"imgui.integrations subpackage — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.integrations.html\"},{\"title\":\"tessl/pypi-imgui@2.0.x - Registry - Tessl\",\"url\":\"https://tessl.io/registry/tessl/pypi-imgui/2.0.0\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/doc/examples/integrations_glfw3.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/doc/examples/integrations_glfw3.py\"},{\"title\":\"How to use the imgui.begin_menu function in imgui | Snyk\",\"url\":\"https://snyk.io/advisor/python/imgui/functions/imgui.begin_menu\"},{\"title\":\"API reference — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/modules.html\"},{\"title\":\"How to use the imgui.render function in imgui | Snyk\",\"url\":\"https://snyk.io/advisor/python/imgui/functions/imgui.render\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about imgui_bundle, Python, frame management, and GlfwRenderer:\n\n## Frame Management with imgui_bundle and GlfwRenderer\n\nThe typical frame management pattern involves polling events, processing inputs, calling `imgui.new_frame()`, defining UI elements, and then rendering. Here's the basic workflow:\n\n### Frame Lifecycle\n\nImGui doesn't draw immediately when you call functions; calls to window and widget functions create entries in a drawing commands list to be executed during next frame rendering, and you decide when to start a new frame context and when to execute all drawing commands.\n\n### Typical Usage Pattern\n\nThe main loop typically includes `glfw.poll_events()`, `impl.process_inputs()`, `imgui.new_frame()`, UI definition code, and then rendering.\n\n### Key Functions\n\nFor frame management, the essential functions are:\n\n- `new_frame()` - starts a new frame context, `end_frame()` - ends the frame, and `render()` - executes drawing commands\n- `GlfwRenderer.process_inputs()` - handles input processing for the frame\n- `GlfwRenderer.render(draw_data)` - renders the accumulated drawing commands\n\nWhen using a pure Python backend with GLFW, you need to call `imgui.backends.opengl3_new_frame()` after loading fonts as part of the initialization.\n\nThe `GlfwRenderer` class handles the OpenGL rendering backend, while the frame management functions (`new_frame()`, `render()`, `end_frame()`) control when ImGui processes input and generates drawing commands for each frame.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"ba2efcff-f8ca-4609-971a-c3a78cf8c6a9"}
