{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015M4QiuFVA34uhnPGdKRz6g","type":"tool_result","content":"# Demo Docking Application Overview\n\nThis Python file demonstrates a sophisticated ImGui application with advanced layout and UI management features.\n\n## Key Components\n\n**Application Architecture:**\nThe demo implements a complete application structure with state management through an `AppState` class that tracks application variables, fonts, and UI state across execution cycles.\n\n**Docking System:**\nThe application showcases multiple customizable dock layouts. It creates separate dock spaces (CommandSpace, CommandSpace2, MiscSpace) that organize windows hierarchically. Users can switch between three predefined layouts: Default, Alternative, and Tabs layouts.\n\n**Widget Examples:**\nThe code demonstrates essential ImGui widgets including:\n- `imgui.slider_float()` and `imgui.slider_int()` for numeric input\n- `imgui.button()` for interactive controls\n- `imgui.checkbox_flags()` for toggle options\n- `imgui.input_text_multiline()` for text editing\n- Progress bars and status indicators\n\n**Font Management:**\nCustom font loading supports multiple typefaces: title fonts (Roboto), emoji fonts (NotoEmoji), icon fonts (FontAwesome), and colored fonts (Playbox). This illustrates advanced text rendering capabilities.\n\n**Features Demonstrated:**\n- Theme customization and application styling\n- Status bar implementation\n- Custom menu systems\n- Borderless, movable windows\n- Dynamic window creation during runtime\n- User settings persistence in INI files\n\nThe implementation serves as a comprehensive reference for building feature-rich ImGui applications in Python."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"f52b019e-edac-42d2-908b-4539973eb851"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CF4iYpR5SgGxqM7VUxY4Sm","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python \"color_button\" OR \"color_edit\" color widget examples\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"imgui.core module — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.core.html\"},{\"title\":\"imgui-bundle · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/imgui-bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pthom/imgui_bundle: From expressive code to powerful GUIs in no time: a fast, feature-rich, cross-platform toolkit for C++ & Python.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"Dear ImGui Bundle - Dear ImGui Bundle\",\"url\":\"https://pthom.github.io/imgui_bundle/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle: Dear ImGui Bundle: easily create ImGui applications in Python and C++. Batteries included!\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gmh5225/imgui-imgui_bundle\"},{\"title\":\"How to use the imgui.push_style_color function in imgui | Snyk\",\"url\":\"https://snyk.io/advisor/python/imgui/functions/imgui.push_style_color\"},{\"title\":\"ImGui Color Text Edit | pthom/imgui_bundle | DeepWiki\",\"url\":\"https://deepwiki.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/6.5-imgui-color-text-edit\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/doc/examples/testwindow.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/doc/examples/testwindow.py\"},{\"title\":\"ImGui Windows and Widgets Colors | HackLAB\",\"url\":\"https://www.geeks3d.com/hacklab/20180217/imgui-windows-and-widgets-colors/\"},{\"title\":\"Contents — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about color widget examples in imgui/imgui_bundle Python bindings:\n\n## Color Button Examples\n\nThe `color_button` function can be used like: `imgui.color_button(\"Button 1\", 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 10, 10)` to create color buttons with different colors and dimensions.\n\nYou can also iterate through style colors and display them: `for color in range(0, imgui.COLOR_COUNT): imgui.text(\"Color: {}\".format(color)); imgui.color_button(\"color#{}\".format(color), *style.colors[color])`.\n\n## Color Edit Examples\n\nThe `color_edit4` function displays a color edit widget for colors with alpha values.\n\nAn example with color_edit4 shows: storing color data outside the loop (e.g., `color = 1., .0, .5, 1.`), then using `_, color = imgui.color_edit4(\"Alpha\", *color)` which returns a tuple indicating if the color changed and the current color/alpha values.\n\n## Additional Resources\n\nFor more comprehensive examples, the source code for demos can be found in `bindings/imgui_bundle/demos_python` and the `demo_imgui_bundle` serves as a manual with lots of examples and related code. The interactive manual showcases almost every part of the bundle with runnable examples where you can inspect and copy C++ and Python source code for each demo.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"afe3447a-919d-4802-ba73-cec881df8c1c"}
