{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FA7R7FDRM1EFJeFCEuFkea","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"imgui_bundle Python \"glfw_backend\" \"GlfwRenderer\" initialization example\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"imgui_bundle/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py at main · pthom/imgui_bundle\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pthom/imgui_bundle/blob/main/bindings/imgui_bundle/python_backends/examples/example_python_backend_glfw3.py\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/doc/source/gen_example.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/doc/source/gen_example.py\"},{\"title\":\"A simple pyimgui example using the GLFW backend · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://gist.github.com/DGriffin91/c986d9bce5a0549d6e5c207261636e62\"},{\"title\":\"First steps with imgui — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guide/first-steps.html\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/doc/examples/integrations_glfw3.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/doc/examples/integrations_glfw3.py\"},{\"title\":\"pyimgui/imgui/integrations/glfw.py at master · pyimgui/pyimgui\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pyimgui/pyimgui/blob/master/imgui/integrations/glfw.py\"},{\"title\":\"imgui.integrations subpackage — pyimgui 2.0.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyimgui.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference/imgui.integrations.html\"},{\"title\":\"Comprehensive Guide to ImGui and Python: Build Modern GUIs with Ease\",\"url\":\"https://betanet.net/view-post/comprehensive-guide-to-imgui-and-python\"},{\"title\":\"concur.integrations.glfw API documentation\",\"url\":\"https://potocpav.github.io/python-concur-docs/master/integrations/glfw.html\"},{\"title\":\"tessl/pypi-imgui@2.0.x - Registry - Tessl\",\"url\":\"https://tessl.io/registry/tessl/pypi-imgui/2.0.0\"}]\n\nI found several relevant examples for initializing `GlfwRenderer` with imgui_bundle and pyimgui. Here's what the search results show:\n\n## Basic Initialization Pattern\n\nThe typical initialization involves creating an imgui context, initializing GLFW, and then instantiating a GlfwRenderer with the window object. Here's the core pattern:\n\n```python\nimport imgui\nfrom imgui.integrations.glfw import GlfwRenderer\nimport glfw\n\n# Create context\nimgui.create_context()\n\n# Initialize GLFW window\nwindow = impl_glfw_init()  # Your GLFW window setup function\n\n# Initialize GlfwRenderer\nimpl = GlfwRenderer(window)\n```\n\n## Constructor Details\n\nThe GlfwRenderer constructor takes a window parameter and an optional attach_callbacks boolean parameter (defaulting to True), which automatically attaches keyboard, mouse, resize, character, and scroll callbacks to the window.\n\n## Main Loop Example\n\nWithin the main loop, you should call glfw.poll_events(), impl.process_inputs(), and imgui.new_frame() before rendering.\n\nA complete basic example shows initializing GLFW, creating the window, creating an imgui context, instantiating GlfwRenderer, and then in the main loop calling poll_events(), process_inputs(), new_frame(), creating ImGui windows/content, then calling render() and swap_buffers().\n\nThe first search result appears to be from the official imgui_bundle repository with a full working example if you'd like to see more details.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"b9639b10-90c3-48f7-a8e9-b254d956fafe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LANKAs21jdNnHfEbqrCkSM","type":"tool_result","content":"# PyImGui Core Module Reference\n\nThis documentation covers **pyimgui 2.0.0**, a Python wrapper for Dear ImGui that enables creation of immediate mode graphical user interfaces.\n\n## Key Classes\n\n**_IO**: The main ImGui I/O context for configuration. Accessible via `imgui.get_io()`, it manages input/output, fonts, and metrics.\n\n**_FontAtlas**: Manages font loading and control. Access through `get_io().fonts` to add default fonts or load TTF files.\n\n**_DrawList**: Low-level drawing API obtained via `get_window_draw_list()`. Supports primitives like circles, rectangles, lines, bezier curves, and text rendering.\n\n**GuiStyle**: Provides access to ImGui styling parameters including colors, spacing, padding, and rounding values.\n\n## Core Window Functions\n\n- `begin()` / `end()`: Create standard windows\n- `begin_child()` / `end_child()`: Scrollable regions with flexible sizing\n- `begin_popup()` / `end_popup()`: Non-modal popups\n- `begin_popup_modal()`: Modal dialogs that overlay other content\n- `begin_main_menu_bar()`: Full-screen menu bars\n\n## Input & Interaction\n\nThe API includes comprehensive input handling: mouse position/clicks, keyboard state, drag-and-drop support, and item focus detection via functions like `is_item_hovered()`, `is_mouse_clicked()`, and `is_key_pressed()`.\n\n## Widgets\n\nStandard controls include buttons, sliders, checkboxes, text input, combo boxes, and tree nodes. Color editing supports both RGB and HSV formats.\n\nMost functions return context managers suitable for `with` statements, automatically handling begin/end pairing."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"948d2a9d-a536-4a27-90d6-35cedadb3a46"}
