{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018LgomonNLZHiA2XSeBCkXP","type":"tool_result","content":"# PyImGui: Getting Started\n\n## What is Immediate Mode GUI?\n\nPyImGui is a Python wrapper for the ImGui C++ library that enables you to build custom user interfaces with any game engine or graphics library. Unlike retained mode systems, immediate mode GUI libraries construct the drawing pipeline on-the-fly. As the documentation explains, this approach means \"defining whole GUI on every frame may seem counterintuitive and inefficient\" yet offers flexibility and rapid iteration.\n\n## Core Components\n\nThe library has two main parts:\n\n1. **imgui.core** - Provides functions for creating windows, widgets, and managing GUI state\n2. **imgui.integrations** - Supplies backend integrations with popular frameworks\n\n## Basic Rendering Loop\n\nA minimal implementation follows this pattern:\n\n```python\nimport imgui\n\nimgui.create_context()\nimgui.get_io().display_size = 100, 100\nimgui.get_io().fonts.get_tex_data_as_rgba32()\n\nimgui.new_frame()\nimgui.begin(\"Your first window!\", True)\nimgui.text(\"Hello world!\")\nimgui.end()\nimgui.render()\nimgui.end_frame()\n```\n\n## Backend Integration\n\nPyImGui supports multiple rendering backends including GLFW, pygame, SDL2, Cocos2d, pyglet, and OpenGL. Install with specific backends using pip:\n\n```bash\npip install imgui[sdl2]\npip install imgui[glfw,cocos2d,pygame,sdl2,pyglet]\n```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"3d0d32d6-6462-4080-b1f1-9f1a5dde7d6c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FifRLXcLHaxp5SdGLuYddP","type":"tool_result","content":"# PyImGui Integrations Overview\n\nThe `imgui.integrations` subpackage provides renderer implementations for various graphics and windowing frameworks. Key components include:\n\n## Main Renderers\n\n**GlfwRenderer** handles GLFW window integration with callbacks for keyboard input, character events, window resizing, mouse interactions, and scroll events. It includes a `process_inputs()` method for input handling.\n\n**OpenGL Support** offers two renderer options:\n- `ProgrammablePipelineRenderer` for modern OpenGL with shader-based rendering\n- `FixedPipelineRenderer` for legacy OpenGL implementations\n\nBoth include methods to \"refresh the font texture\" and render draw data, plus utility functions to backup and restore OpenGL state.\n\n**Cross-Platform Backends** include implementations for:\n- **Pygame**: Features `process_event()` and `process_inputs()` methods\n- **SDL2**: Provides \"basic SDL2 integration implementation\" with mouse wheel scaling and event processing\n- **Cocos2d**: Offers an ImguiLayer class marked as an event handler\n- **Compute utility**: A `compute_fb_scale()` function for framebuffer scaling calculations\n\nEach renderer handles framework-specific event processing and rendering pipeline management for seamless ImGui integration across different graphics libraries."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BrXVphQwDP4yDAgTWGvdeC","session_id":"b723e047-a0d7-4deb-a7c3-8c0b4525f837","uuid":"611b5c22-12c3-43de-bc44-e009d41e8cc3"}
